<br>
I do try hard to be polite, and one of the things I do to be polite is generally to do as much of the work as possible for a cleric.  So if I need a rez, I usually haul my carcass to a zone and ask the next cleric who comes through if they would be so kind as to click/cast on me.  Or I will take my slowly rotting husk over to the place where the cleric is grouped/farming/scratching their arse ask politely if they would mind, and then wait patiently until they are available.<br>
<br>
I offer a full mana bar worth of buffs for them / their group, not like I can keep the mana anyway.  I also offer peridots to those who are willing to accept.<br>
<br>
I never viewed it as waving my corspe in someones face though, just trying to inconvenience the cleric as little as possible. <p><center><img src="http://cleric.homestead.com/files/mathi.jpg" border="0">
</a> </center>
