All the way.  Its true that people will still be able to identify you by your gear.  Plus you have your friends who know your class.  But I don't mind buffing people near me.  Its just the ones I don't know who expect me to cross the entire zone, or wait 15 minutes while they do the same that I really care to avoid.  Oh yeah, I also don't like saying no to people, so going role is how I avoid the pickup group requests while I am trying to form guildies/friends groups of my own.  /shrug<br>
